sentences: Formed by Marvin Vriesde and Hassan M9echtar in 1996, they got their first big break when their debut demo titled "The Plot Sickens..." got a great review in Terrorizer magazine, which caught the eye of Earache Records label manager Dan Tobin.
Torch released their self titled debut album on Wicked World in 1999.
Torch and Wicked World parted ways in 2001.
Torch entered the prestigious regional talent competition, De Grote Prijs van Zuid-Holland (The Grand Prize of South Holland) in 2004., which they won.
Still unsigned, the band released another full length album titled "Volatile" in 2004.
In 2005, guitarist Marvin Vriesde left the band to focus on his other band, Severe Torture.
The band released another full length album, Volatile, Currently unsigned, they had been signed with Earache Records, and have released two full-length albums.
After a demo, they recorded an eponymous album, which was picked up by Wicked World, a sublabel of Earache Records, who signed the band in 2000.
In July 2005, Vriesde left the band (he is also active in Dew-Scented) and was replaced by Rory Hansen, formerly of Bagga Bownz.
The band's website announced in 2006 that Sander Koole, longtime bassist for the band, left to pursue other musical interests.
Since 7 October 2006, the band's website has not been updated.
